        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Count tiles before panicking:</span> If tile tracking shows your opponent can't reach the TWS (wrong tiles for the needed word), save the block for later. Don't waste scoring turns on phantom threats.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Block the closer TWS first:</span> A TWS 2 squares from existing tiles is an immediate threat. One 6 squares away can wait. Prioritize by proximity and accessibility.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Use the TWS yourself if possible:</span> The best defense is offense. If you can reach the TWS with a decent word, take it — you score big AND deny it to your opponent simultaneously.</p>
